european partners and japan have a stake in gorbachev succeeding 
they would argue he has lowered tensions while also trying to 
improve conditions at home 
failure could usher in a hardline successor 
others argue that the west should keep its distance and let the 
soviets figure their own way out of difficulty 
collectively the bush administration is not sure yet but thats 
the direction in which it appears to be going as baker huddles with 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze in wyoming 
