<TEXT>
the american indian dance theater its 23 dancers 
and musicians coming from 17 tribes is presenting a fascinating 
twohour show through oct 1 at the joyce theater 
the 15 dances seen thursday night are said to be authentic 
traditional indian dances staged by hanay geiogamah a member of 
the kiowadelaware tribes from oklahoma and raoul trujillo 
one can enjoy them as dance or study them more deeply for 
meaning an explanation of each dance is written in the program 
hoop dance a solo by eddie swimmer a cherokee from north 
carolina is remarkable while dancing he picks up thin metal hoops 
and puts them around his body knees and arms at various angles 
until he looks like a man inside a cage notes say he has danced 
with 42 hoops 
six men with eagle wings down their arms performed eagle 
dance as they walked through steam they seemed to be soaring 
over clouds in a second version as danced in another region they 
would squat and stand again seeming to fly 
many of the dances had face paint elaborate costumes in sunburst 
colors much fringe and headdresses dance steps were often a step 
and hesitation or step and hop our interest was held less by the 
costumes than on the countless interesting variations of movement 
in buffalo dance fabian fontenelle from the zuni pueblo in 
new mexico who also plays drums with a rock group satschals and 
morgan tosee a member of the comanche tribe had furcovered heads 
