<TEXT>
a food and drug administration advisory 
committee on friday recommended strengthening warnings against side 
effects of the worlds leading sleep medication halcion to 
indicate a possibly greater risk of temporary amnesia than other 
drugs in its class 
the panel also recommended stronger warnings concerning possible 
side effects of all hypnotic sleep drugs 
the recommendations resulted from the psychopharmacological drugs 
advisory committees review of a relatively high number reports 
about side effects associated with the use of halcion compared with 
other sedativehypnotics the reports included amnesia anxiety 
aggression and hallucinations all of which are included in the 
current warning label for the drug 
the panel recommended a stronger warning on amnesia only 
the fda has six months to act on the recommendations 
panel members said the number of adverse reactions reported may 
not be an indication that halcion carries greater risks of unwanted 
side effects than other drugs in its class 
given the limitations of the information we did not sense 
there was a special problem of side effects with halcion said dr 
daniel e casey panel chairman and chief of psychiatric research 
and psychopharmacology at the veterans administration medical center 
in portland ore 
since halcion was approved for sale in the united states in 1983 
about 43 million prescriptions of the drug have been written and the 
fda has received 1693 reports of adverse side effects possibly 
associated with use of the drug ranging from amnesia to death said 
charles anello deputy director of the fdas office of epidemiology 
and biostatistics 
by comparison 35 million prescriptions have been written for 
restoril a sedativehypnotic made by sandoz pharmaceuticals corp 
since 1981 and the fda has received 266 reports of unwanted side 
effects he said 
officials of the upjohn co which makes halcion said the higher 
reports for halcion are probably partly due to media reports about 
the drug 
publicity about the drug included an article in california 
magazine a year ago by a woman who entitled her experience with the 
drug halcion nightmare network television features about the 
drug and reporting on a case last year in which a utah woman shot 
her mother after having taken halcion charges against the woman 
were dismissed 
upjohn spokesman godfrey grant said the company was pleased the 
advisory committee has essentially come to the conclusion that there 
are few if any concerns that need to be addressed 
the epidemiological data upjohn presented to the panel does not 
support a significant problem but we did acknowledge there could be 
some concern with inappropriate dosing he said referring to 
higher doses of the drug 
there is no emergency and we dont see a public health 
hazard said paul leber director of the fdas division of 
neuropharmacological drug products 
though the committee agreed to recommend a specific relabeling 
for halcion to note that it may carry a greater risk than other 
hypnotics for temporary amnesia the panel also decided to address 
concerns for the entire class of sleeping pills three drugs are 
included in this class halcion restoril and dalmane made by 
roche products inc 
committee members said they were concerned about travelers 
amnesia a temporary amnesia that can affect travelers who take 
one of the sleep drugs when they awake they can function normally 
but later wont recall their activities during this period such as 
going through customs at the airport leber said 
the labels for these drugs already warn of amnesia as a possible 
side effect but the committee recommended the fda consider adding 
mention of travelers amnesia to the labels 
panel members also asked the fda to provide material to 
consumers to alert to the possibility of side effects of the 
sedativehypnotic drugs so consumers could discuss these with their 
doctor 
this could be expressed in many different ways panel 
chairman casey said 
</TEXT>
