nasa said friday that it still hopes 
to launch space shuttle atlantis on schedule oct 12 despite 
disruptions caused by hurricane hugo 
officials had said thursday the launch probably would be 
postponed at least two days because of preparations made to move 
atlantis off the launch pad to the safety of an assembly building in 
case the storm headed this way 
that effort was halted early thursday when hugo passed harmlessly 
300 miles east of here 
electrical communications and fuel line connections between the 
pad and shuttle had been disconnected in case a move became 
necessary those had to be reattached and retested a task expected 
to add at least two days to the launch preparation time the 
officials had said 
the schedule is tight but we feel we still have a chance to 
make the oct 12 date nasa spokeswoman lisa malone said friday 
a firm launch date will be set on oct 3 following a twoday 
flight readiness review by shuttle managers 
