adn said all the conference participants agreed that every 
party works out and realizes independently its own political line 
its strategy and tactics they are responsible to their own people 
it said the ideologists emphasized that such questions as 
economic growth development of political systems the raising of 
living standards and guarantees of human rights and freedoms are 
being raised in discussions of the perfection remodeling or 
renewal of socialism 
attending the conference in addition to warsaw pact members east 
germany hungary poland bulgaria romania the soviet union and 
czechoslovakia were representatives from vietnam north korea 
cuba laos and mongolia according to adn 
jan fojtik chief ideologist of czechoslovakias communist party 
was quoted by the czechoslovak news agency ctk as saying the meeting 
had shown that different approaches are no obstacle to mutual 
understanding and to the development of cooperation 
ctk reported fojtik said it was necessary to achieve mutual 
understanding while respecting the specific conditions of 
development in the member countries 
czechoslovakia sided with east germany in denouncing hungary for 
opening its borders to thousands of east germans seeking to emigrate 
to the west 
