<TEXT>
music fans no longer have to judge a record 
by its cover 
a new company is offering consumers the chance to sample portions 
of albums using their touchtone telephones at 89 cents a minute a 
nimblefingered fan can form musical opinions for less than the cost 
of a single 
with the cost of compact discs and the large market out there 
this gives a listener a chance to hear an album before he buys it 
said mark munson marketing director for music systems inc 
the fort lauderdale fla company has been operating its special 
charge 900 telephone line since the beginning of august about 5000 
people a week are calling to hear a little music munson said 
music line is the little brother of the party lines and rock 
hotlines that have boomed in popularity during the past few years 
with advancing telephone technology 
callers who hook into the system are asked to choose from among 
more than 100 albums in categories such as rock heavy metal rap 
progressive and socalled black music 
once the selection is made a 10 to 15second snippet of each 
song on the album is played callers can move on to another song or 
album with the press of a button the average caller stays on the 
line for about four minutes 
we sampled the 15 seconds that hopefully are the most 
indicative of the song munson said we dont just start at the 
beginning 
albums on the playlist range from such hit artists as fine young 
cannibals the traveling wilburys and madonna to more obscure 
newcomers such as rappers three times dope and independent label 
rockers nirvana 
a group of harvard business school students were the brains 
behind the idea they started a telephone line in the early 1980s 
but it folded due to high costs a 900 telephone line is considered 
easier and cheaper to run 
with radio stations increasingly reluctant to play more than one 
or two songs from an album music line performs an important 
service munson said 
one act thats generated a lot of calls he said is elektra 
records recording artists 10000 maniacs curious fans can easily 
find out through music line that despite the name 10000 maniacs is 
actually a literate folkrock band he said 
elektra is intrigued by the idea that they are on the system 
munson said that kind of a response is good they see it as a 
valuable service 
but the groups manager peter leak said hes not certain he 
likes the idea of someone outside the group boiling down 10000 
maniacs songs into the 15 seconds they consider most important 
hearing 15 seconds of each song on each album isnt hearing the 
whole album said leak whose new york end ltd also manages the 
cowboy junkies another band featured on music line to imagine 
that it does is not being realistic 
its much preferable he said for a fan to slip on a pair of 
headphones in a record store and hear as much of the album as 
possible many record stores used to have listening booths where 
customers could do this 
music line has no formal relationship with record companies but 
marketing departments in several companies are eagerly providing the 
phone service with compact discs and promotional materials munson 
said 
thats obviously in their best interests he said because 
listeners who like the 15second snippets will go out and buy the 
records 
