weve been approached but we have absolutely no idea what the 
potential of this thing is said robert altshuler spokesman for 
cbs records whose records are being used on music line its too 
early this is a brand new thing 
the service helps record companies in the same way radio play 
does said louis dennis national sales director for warner bros 
records whose lps are also being used 
obviously the more exposure we get the better we are dennis 
said whether this is a revolutionary thing i dont know 
but dennis said when he first saw advertisements for music line 
he alerted warner bros legal department munson said thats been 
the initial reaction of several record companies whose persnickety 
attitude toward unauthorized use of their product has been seen in 
the controversy over home taping 
im not saying they dont have the rights to do it leak said 
of the service im sure they do id like to make sure that there 
are some provisions that people get taken care of it seems a little 
unfair that all the money flows into one pocket 
music line pays a small fee to music publishing firms for use of 
the songs munson said the company is relying on a legal opinion 
that says it owes record companies nothing he said 
if any record company feels they dont want the album on the 
system well take it off the system he said of course its 
in their best interests to be on the system its a new thing and 
of course people always have questions about new things 
the company also wants to assuage the fears of parents who worry 
about teenagers rolling up exorbitant phone bills at a parents 
request the company can block calls coming in from a particular 
phone line munson said the company also offers a moneyback 
guarantee to dissatisfied customers although the process would take 
a few months he added 
the phone service which drew more than 12500 calls in its first 
month has an eventual goal of 2500 calls a day munson said 
