<TEXT>
at first glance they appear vastly different a 
singer and television star turned successful businessman and a high 
school dropout who built his way up to become a millionaire 
developer 
but merv griffin and robert campeau to their chagrin have much 
in common both men find their companies struggling because they 
cant handle debts run up in notorious takeover battles 
griffins resorts international inc is trying to restructure a 
900 million debt after failing to meet interest payments to 
bondholders resorts which operates hotels and casinos is not 
generating enough cash to pay bills 
campeau meanwhile was forced to cede control of his retailing 
empire to olympia amp york developments ltd in exchange for a 250 
million loan 
his company campeau corp also could not meet interest payments 
on some of its 115 billion debt and the developer has had to put 
his prize bloomingdales department store chain up for sale 
resorts has attributed some of its problems to competition from 
newer casinos in atlantic city poor management and deteriorating 
physical facilities 
campeaus federated department stores inc and allied stores 
corp have suffered from the same lackluster sales that have 
afflicted other retailers 
but the real problem is that merv griffin and robert campeau paid 
too much for their companies went too deeply into debt and did not 
anticipate that their cash flow would be inadequate to handle their 
interest payments 
griffin battled with developer donald trump over resorts for 
months last year with onagain offagain agreements before finally 
buying the company for 364 million and the assumption of 600 
million in debt griffin issued 325 million in notes to help 
finance the deal 
