<TEXT>
opec ministers gathering for weekend talks on the 
oil market appeared at odds friday over whether to lift their 
production ceiling in the final three months of the year 
even before the start of discussions scheduled for late saturday 
some ministers arriving in geneva expressed concern over what they 
consider to be weak crude prices eight ministers comprising the 
organization of petroleum exporting countries price monitoring and 
longterm strategy committee are scheduled to meet 
an increase in opec production which some believe the ministers 
might authorize would likely cause prices to slip analysts say 
theres no need to raise the ceiling as long as the price 
objective is not met said algerian oil minister sadek boussena 
but issam abdul raheem alchalabi iraqs oil chief said i 
would like to see a reasonable increase in the ceiling he didnt 
specify a level 
however observers as well as some opec ministers have said they 
dont expect a resolution to the volatile issue of permanent quotas 
at this latest meeting instead it appeared the quota issue would 
be bumped to november when the full cartel is to meet in vienna 
we can always discuss it but there will not be a decision in 
this area said boussena 
the 13nation cartel is pumping about 22 million barrels a day 
according to various estimates well over the output cap of 195 
million barrels set by opec for the last six months of the year 
the ministers agreed in june to meet this month to decide whether 
to lift the ceiling 500000 barrels a day to 20 million barrels or 
perhaps more 
although world oil prices are weaker than they were last spring 
and remain below the catels benchmark of 18 a barrel strong 
demand has kept them surprisingly firm despite opecs excess 
production 
opec secretarygeneral subroto has estimated that demand for the 
cartels oil might be around 22 million barrels a day in the 
octoberdecember quarter 
a basket of seven crudes monitored by opec averaged 1704 a 
barrel last week it had topped the 18mark last spring 
west texas intermediate the benchmark grade of american oil has 
been trading in the range of 1950 to 20 a 42gallon barrel 
chalabi arriving in midafternoon from an energy conference in 
montreal told reporters that the opec ministers would review 
conditions in the constantly changing oil market 
he said some countries were opposed to an output increase because 
they want to defend the price others he said think supply 
and demand warrant a much higher ceiling 
boussena said there was a link between the cartels 
production level and its price and he noted that prices had not 
reached opecs benchmark in the last three months 
ecuadors diego tamariz also seemed worried about prices 
we still have to obtain the goal of 18 he said adding that 
we should work on it 
fergus macleod an analyst at the investment firm of barclays de 
zoete wedd in london said prices would likely fall 50 cents or a 
dollar a barrel if the cartel were to lift the supply cap without 
curtailing members cheating 
an increase of 500000 barrels a day he said would probably 
kick up total output to about 225 million barrels 
the ministers were also expected to begin tackling the tough 
issue of how to meet some members demands for a higher share of the 
production pie each country is given a quota or a daily production 
level 
kuwait and the united arab emirates have in recent months ignored 
their quotas and pumped as much as double their shares of about a 
million barrels each analysts estimate 
kuwaits oil minister ali khalifa alsabah said his promise at 
the june meeting to hold the line on production was conditional 
if everybody sticks to the quota fine if anybody breaks it 
the others have the same right he told reporters outside the 
luxury hotel where the ministers will hold their discussions 
the talks will technically be held by a monitoring panel of 
ministers from algeria indonesia iran iraq kuwait nigeria 
saudi arabia and venezuela the others gabon ecuador libya 
qatar and the united arab emirates were also invited to attend 
saudia arabias oil minister hisham nazer was reported 
recovering from surgery in the united states and was not attending 
