the michelin group of france announced friday 
it will acquire uniroyal goodrich tire co in a deal valued at 15 
billion forming the largest tiremaker in the world 
michelin will pay 690 million for uniroyal goodrich and assume 
810 million in debt company officials said 
we are confident that michelins additional financial and 
technological resources will make an important contribution to the 
uniroyal goodrich tire cos future uniroyal goodrich chairman b 
charles ames said 
ames also is a principal in the new york investment firm clayton 
amp dubilier inc which acquired uniroyal inc in 1985 to help it 
thwart a hostile takeover by carl c icahn 
uniroyal goodrich will operate as a subsidiary of the michelin 
group and will keep its headquarters in akron the company will 
continue to make and distribute uniroyal bfgoodrich and other 
brands of tires while retaining its corporate identity michelin 
spokesman jim morton said 
michelin based in clermonterrand france was locked in a 
threeway contest with akronbased goodyear tire amp rubber co and 
bridgestone of japan to be the worlds largest tire company 
but michelin would become the largest if regulators in the united 
states and canada approve the deal said saul ludwig a tire analyst 
with clevelandbased raulston amp co 
the michelin group reported 1988 sales of 87 billion uniroyal 
goodrich had sales of 22 billion in 1988 for a total of 109 
billion goodyear had sales of 108 billion in 1988 
we expect to see positive results both shortterm and 
longterm when michelins technology and research are added to our 
own capabilities said sheldon r salzman uniroyal goodrich 
president and chief operating officer 
this transaction will mean continued job security for our 
employees and a stronger uniroyal goodrich in the future he said 
clayton amp dubilier took uniroyal private in a managementled 950 
million buyout martin h dubilier chairman of clayton amp dubilier 
said the company knew a partner would be needed 
michelin approached us dubilier said they have the 
resources to make us more competitive 
dubilier estimated uniroyal goodrich will need to spend 600 
million in the next five years to remain competitive in the tire 
business 
uniroyal goodrich became the secondlargest tire manufacturer in 
north america and fifthlargest worldwide when bf goodrich co and 
uniroyal inc of middlebury conn merged their tire operations in 
august 1986 
michelin group operates michelin tire corp headquartered in 
greenville sc with four tire manufacturing plants in south 
carolina and plants in alabama and north carolina employing about 
12000 people 
michelin tires ltd a subsidiary of michelin group operates 
three tire manufacturing facilities in nova scotia and employs 4000 
people in canada 
uniroyal goodrich employs 18500 in its tire textile and 
synthetic rubber businesses the company operates tire factories in 
ardmore okla eau claire wis fort wayne ind opelika ala 
and tuscaloosa ala the company also operates two factories in 
kitchener ontario and two in mexico 
michelin said uniroyal goodrich will continue to have its own 
board of directors and retain its corporate identity 
